# Code Quality

Never write code that "just works."

Write code that is:

- readable
- maintainable
- testable
- minimal
- scalable

Avoid:

- nested if statements
- giant components
- giant functions
- magic numbers
- magic strings
- duplicated code
- unnecessary comments

Functions should do one thing.

Components should do one thing.

Prefer composition over complexity.
